premise_source_doc_sentence: CT scan - makes use of computer-processed combinations of many X-ray images taken from different angles to produce cross-sectional  (  tomographic  )  images  (  virtual `` slices ''  )  of specific areas of a scanned object , allowing the user to see inside the object without cutting .

A CT scan makes use of computer-processed combinations of many X-ray images taken from different angles to produce cross-sectional  (  tomographic  )  images  (  virtual `` slices ''  )  of specific areas of a scanned object , allowing the user to see inside the object without cutting .

X-ray computed tomography - makes use of computer-processed combinations of many X-ray images taken from different angles to produce cross-sectional  (  tomographic  )  images  (  virtual `` slices ''  )  of specific areas of a scanned object , allowing the user to see inside the object without cutting .
